Title: This week in Nushell #272
Path: Nushell
Content:
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14258] removed 
``as_i64``
 and 
``as_f64``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14166] made 
``to text``
 line endings consistent for list (streams)
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14157] overhauled div, mod, and floor div
aionescu 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14283] removed unneeded clones in 
``select``
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14281] updated reedline to the latest commit
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14266] updated human-date-parser conversion to use local timezone
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14263] allowed != for polars
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14114] prevented IR from generating unnecessary instructions for 
``def``
 and 
``export def``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14101] fixed $env.FILE_PWD and $env.CURRENT_FILE inside 
``use``
weirdan 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14275] fixed the order of preference for 
``VISUAL``
 and 
``EDITOR``
132ikl 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14255] improved Nushell's handling of case-insensitive string handling
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14250] consolidated uses of 
``test-case``
 to 
``rstest``
CharlesTaylor7 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14246] made empty rest args match an empty list
alex-kattathra-johnson 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14245] added tests for the 
``--max-age``
 arg in http commands
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14237] changed --max-time arg for http commands to use 
``Duration``
 type
NotTheDr01ds 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14242] stopped autoloading deprecated-dirs
Bahex 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14239] added table params support to 
``url join``
 and 
``url build-query``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14211] implemented a new 
``url split-query``
 command
sgvictorino 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14231] excluded import path from args to aliased external commands
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14226] correctly parsed table literals as lists
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14224] added support for binary input in 
``length``
Dorumin 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14214] removed a deref in 
``touch``
